Write a method named printAverage that accepts a Scanner for the console as a parameter 
and repeatedly prompts the user for numbers. Once any number less than zero is typed, 
the average of all non-negative numbers typed is displayed. Display the average as a double, 
and do not round it. For example, a call to your method might look like this:


Scanner console = new Scanner(System.in);
printAverage(console);
The following is one example log of execution for your method:

Type a number: 7
Type a number: 4
Type a number: 16
Type a number: -4
Average was 9.0
If the first number typed is negative, do not print an average. For example:

Type a number: -2


public static void printAverage (Scanner console)
{
    System.out.print("Type a number: ");
    int num = console.nextInt();
    
    if (num < 0)
    {
        return;
    }
    
    int sum = 0;
    int count = 0;
    
    while (num >= 0)
    {
        sum = sum + num;
        count++;
        System.out.print("Type a number: ");
        num = console.nextInt();
    }
    
    System.out.println("Average was " + ((double) sum / count));
}
